A greater acquaintance with the Corporation archives than it was possible for Mr. Riley to have obtained, has amply verified his remarks upon the absence of anything worthy of the name of a volume. The reason for this is, that the early archives now in existence consist purely and simply of the records of the local courts, royal charters, and original grants from various persons.
